  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Leon Bianco is a charming, family run property right in the heart of San Gimignano in Piazza della Cisterna, meaning the bustling markets, shops and entertainment are literally on your doorstep here. The hotel boasts a rich and interesting history with architecture dating back to the 15<sup>th</sup> Century and the interiors have been thoughtfully finished to complement the beautiful structure. Guestrooms are decorated with typical Tuscan furnishings and light colours, perfectly combining the classical feel of the hotel with a modern touch. We recommend upgrading to a double room, where you’ll look over the inner courtyard or Tuscan Countryside.</p>
<p>This lovely property offers a range of amenities including a small gym and billiards room. The highlight though, has to be the roof terrace where you can gaze over the red buildings of San Gimignano and the Tuscan countryside beyond. During summer, these views can be enjoyed with an al fresco breakfast for a truly memorable start to your day.</p>]]></description>
